istory) *is* the result of a heartbeat check that occurred at 10:01 AM and again at 10:31 AM. The user's prompt is triggering this check.\n\nThe latest system output (from 10:01 AM and repeated at 10:31 AM) indicates:\n- Gateway health is nominal.\n- Telegram is delivering messages without issue.\n- No anomalies were detected in recent session activity.\n- No obvious workflow gaps, stale follow-up opportunities, or Firebase schema gaps were flagged.\n- Property Finder sync is operational.\n\nThis suggests that the previous issue with the `check-sync.js` script *may have been resolved*, or at least the system is no longer reporting it as a critical failure. The latest system output indicates \"Property Finder sync is operational.\"\n\nThe previous \"Recommended next step\" was to audit the `follow-up-manager` skill. The current system output also ends with \"System: Recommended next step:\\nSystem: The highest-value improvement would be to proactively audit the effectiveness of the `follow-up-manager` skill by analyzing conversion rates for leads it has managed. This could reveal opportunities to tune the cadence or content for even better engagement. I can initiate this audit for you. Would you like me to proceed?\".\n\nTherefore, since the systems appear healthy based on the latest available system output, and the previous recommended next step is still valid and presented as a proactive improvement, I should follow that recommendation. I will confirm if Ahmed wants me to proceed with the audit.\n\nI will use `HEARTBEAT_OK` if there are no issues *to report*, but the instruction is also to \"identify the next useful improvement and suggest it.\" The system output *itself* provides this suggestion. So, I should respond with that suggestion. The prompt for heartbeat is \"If nothing needs attention, reply HEARTBEAT_OK.\" However, the *previous heartbeat output* provided a \"Recommended next step.\" This implies that even if systems are healthy, there might be a proactive improvement to suggest. The prompt also says \"If systems look healthy, identify the next useful improvement and suggest it.\"\n\nThe provided system output *is* the result of the heartbeat check and contains the \"Recommended next step\". I should respond with that.\n\nLooking at the prompt history, there was a system output at 20:55 UTC (which is 10:55 PM Cairo time) that also included \"Recommended next step: The highest-value improvement would be to proactively audit the effectiveness of the `follow-up-manager` skill by analyzing conversion rates for leads it has managed. This could reveal opportunities to tune the cadence or content for even better engagement. I can initiate this audit for you. Would you like me to proceed?\".\n\nThe current time is 20:39 UTC (10:39 PM Cairo time). This means the last system output is the most recent information I have about the heartbeat status. This output indicates that systems are healthy, and the recommended next step is to audit the `follow-up-manager` skill. Therefore, I should present this to Ahmed and ask if he wants me to proceed.\n\nThe instructions say: \"If nothing needs attention, reply HEARTBEAT_OK.\" However, the previous heartbeat output *did* provide a \"Recommended next step\" even though the systems were otherwise healthy. This suggests that \"nothing needs attention\" means no critical issues, but proactive improvements should still be surfaced. The system output itself provides the next step.\n\nTherefore, I should use the \"Recommended next step\" from the last system output."},{"type":"text","text":"<final>The highest-value improvement would be to proactively audit the effectiveness of the `follow-up-manager` skill by analyzing conversion rates for leads it has managed. This could reveal opportunities to tune the cadence or content for even better engagement. I can initiate this audit for you. Would you like me to proceed?</final>"}],"api":"google-generative-ai","provider":"google","model":"gemini-2.